Rhythm Section Radio was founded in 2009 and moved to NTS in 2012, and has since pulled out the stops breaking new music, promoting independent labels and paying homage to the greatest music from the past, through a perhaps unhealthy obsession with record digging.

Part of the NTS family since day dot, Moxie has held her Wednesday show since the stations first broadcasts. Inviting esteemed guests for interviews & mixes and breaking new, unreleased music, she’s got your Wednesday afternoons covered… Tune in to hear anything from Soulful House, Garage, Afro beats and all the way through to rolling techno.
After work fun and global tunes with Tash LC and guests every other Wednesday

For someone who wasn't born there, Kenny Dixon Jr. aka Moodymann might be the most Detroit guy to ever exist.  Moving to the motor city from LA at only three weeks old, he has never "truly" left since. His music channels the musical legacy of Black Detroit – transplanted Delta blues, gospel, Motown and Fortune, Stevie Wonder, the Electrifying Mojo and the Belleville Three – with an unassailable verve. His dust-spackled opus "Silentintroduction" has hummed continously in the background of house music since its release in 1997, inspiring generations of producers. 
Two hours of Kenny Dixon Jr. aka Moodymann, selected and mixed by LDLDN. 
Photo: Donavan Glover

In an era of everything at once, Gabrielle Kwarteng is a DJ who weaves stories that often look to the past, while always focusing on possible futures. Dip in to hear a range of dance music from downtempo to deep house to techno rollers - and everything in between.
Fraternal party starters The Twins takeover for regular trips into electroclash, experimental electronics, and Desi sounds, inviting on boundary pushing collaborators and friends.

Croatian DIY label Low Income $quad showcase their catalogue and extended family of producers - Expect neo trance sounds, reworked Memphis rap acapellas, 90s-inspired fast techno and noisy experimentalism.

nts2.n: Perfect Lives and Tezez Tapes: On the Horn - Tapes from Eritrea and Ethiopia
nts2.d:
Record, book and ephemera dealers Perfect Lives link up with archival Eritrean cassette label, Tezez Tapes, for On The Horn. 
Semir from Tezez Tapes shows off their archive in the first hour, with cassettes from 1985-’91, as mostly diasporic Eritrean artists were experimenting with synthesizers, drum machines, and other modern production techniques to recontextualise traditional melodies and songwriting. Perfect Lives step up in the secon dhour with a mix of Eritrean and Ethiopian pop music from their store selection.

subtle.d: Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!
